<subSubSection id="81B6651AFFE0FFE94DD1F852FC9B9293" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="588" pageId="7" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE0FFE64DD1F852FDE594D4" blockId="7.[151,1436,1945,2006]" box="[151,566,1945,1970]" pageId="7" pageNumber="587">
Length. Male: 
<quantity id="0E549B74FFE0FFE64C7BF852FEA994D4" box="[317,378,1945,1970]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
; female: 
<quantity id="0E549B74FFE0FFE64CA6F852FDE194D4" box="[480,562,1945,1970]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE0FFE94D81F876FBCC927B" blockId="7.[151,1436,1945,2006]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="588" pageId="7" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE0FFE64D81F876FDEA94B0" bold="true" box="[199,569,1981,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="587">Colouration and Morphology:</emphasis>
Yellow greenish to pale yellowish in colour (Plate IIG). Crown and face without submarginal fuscous lines (Plate IIG, I). Crown pale yellowish in colour, with greenish fuscous spot on each side of dorsal marginal ridge. Pronotum yellowish green, laterally carinate. Scutellum with three yellowish longitudinal fuscous bands. Crown subangularly produced; triangular. Ocelli on margin next to eyes, prominent. Genae strongly sinuate below eyes. Pronotum as wide as head, laterally carinate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9133691FFEFFFE94D81FEECFC9B9293" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFEFFFE94D81FEECFEE69226" bold="true" box="[199,309,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe long; acute apically, heavily setose in posterior half (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE9493DFEECFB0E9226" box="[1147,1245,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Valve broadly triangular (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE94C52FE87FEBF9203" box="[276,364,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates elongate, broad basally, tapered apically with 7–8 submarginal setae except in apical half (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE94C7AFEA4FE4792EE" box="[316,404,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Connective “Y”-shaped with stem short (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE94E3AFEA4FC0592EE" box="[892,982,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Style with pointed apophysis, digitate, preapical lobe moderately developed (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE94F16FE5FFD7892CB" box="[592,683,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with finger-like dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFEFFFE949F8FE5FFACF92CB" box="[1214,1308,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[181,1414,855,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[164,1428,833,1684]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hecalus veracious sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. valve; F. aedeagus, dorsal view; G. aedeagus lateral view; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242050/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="588">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft long, straight with few serrations above median length dorsally; pair of leaf-like dorsally serrated apical processes, directed cephalad (Figure 8F–G); gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
